{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Salmon Terrine","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line a straight sided loaf tin with baking paper.","Reserve 1 sprig of dill for garnish. Place remaining dill in mixing bowl and chop <b>15 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place salmon in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add trout and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add cream cheese, double cream, eggs, salt and pepper then mix <b>40 sec\/speed 4<b>. Place half of mixture in prepared loaf tin and smooth surface then cover with a layer of 80 g peeled raw prawns.","Add reserved chopped dill to remaining mixture in mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Place mixture on top of prawns in loaf tin and smooth surface. Cover loaf tin with foil and bake for 1 hour (180°C). Meanwhile, fry remaining 20 g prawns in a little oil over a medium heat until pink, then set aside to cool.","Leave tin to cool for 10 minutes then turn upside down onto a serving plate to remove terrine from tin. Leave to cool completely, then garnish with cooked prawns and reserved sprig of dill. Clean mixing bowl and prepare crème fraîche."]},{"title":"Peppered Crème Fraîche","content":["Place sour cream, crème fraîche, green peppercorns, salt, lemon juice and pepper in mixing bowl then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a small serving bowl and serve with slices of terrine."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Salmon Terrine","content":["25 g fresh dill, thick end of stalks removed","500 g fresh salmon fillets, skinless, cut in pieces (5-6 cm)","2 smoked trout fillets, halved (approx. 120 g)","200 g cream cheese","100 g double cream","2 medium eggs","1 tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","100 g prawns, raw, peeled","olive oil, for frying"]},{"title":"Peppered Crème Fraîche","content":["120 g sour cream","200 g crème fraîche","1 Tbsp pickled green peppercorns, rinsed","¼ tsp fine sea salt","1 tsp lemon juice","1 pinch ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r90227","ima